OL,3,CWater cannons deployed on second night
OL,4,Cof unrest in Belfast
OL,6,FMinisters in Northern Ireland's
OL,7,Fpowersharing government have released
OL,8,Fa joint statement condemning
OL,9,F"disorder, violence and intimidation"
OL,10,Fin Belfast on Tuesday night.
OL,12,FThe statement said: "Events on the
OL,13,Fstreets here caused significant harm
OL,14,Fto communities, spread fear and risked
OL,15,Finnocent lives.
OL,17,F"There can be no justification for
OL,18,Fattacking homes, burning family cars,
OL,19,Fdamaging businesses, and damaging our
OL,20,Fpublic transport and our roads. It
OL,21,Ffurthers no cause and benefits no one.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@eO]tD@UOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
